==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hushing
<hw>Hush"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>The process of
washing ore, or of uncovering mineral veins, by a heavy discharge of
water from a reservoir; flushing; -- also called
<altname>booming</altname> and <altname>hydraulic
mining</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Husk</ent>⟦br⟧
